Though it did not produce silverware, '''[[FC Barcelona|Futbol Club Barcelona]]''''s '''2007-08 season''' would mark a period of change within the club, having many firsts and lasts. Most importantly, this would be [[Ronaldinho]]'s last season with the club that had made him famous, being displaced by the coming of [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] legend [[Thierry Henry]]. This season also marked the breakthrough of young talent [[Bojan KrkiÄ]] into the first team, as well as the emergence of [[Lionel Messi]] as one of the team's key players. On the other hand, this would be [[Lilian Thuram]]'s last season as a professional footballer, as well as [[Gianluca Zambrotta]]'s last with the club. 

==Events==
[[Image:Thierry Henry FC Barcelona cropped.jpg|right|thumb|100px|[[Thierry Henry]], a â¬24 million move from [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]].]]

* 25 June: [[Thierry Henry]] moves from [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] to Barcelona for â¬24 million.<ref>[http://www.fcbarcelona.cat/web/english/noticies/futbol/temporada06-07/06/n070625101079.html FCBarcelona.cat: Bienvenu Monsieur Henry]</ref>

* 29 August: Nike will supply Barcelona until 2017-18 season.<ref>[http://www.fcbarcelona.cat/web/english/noticies/club/temporada07-08/08/n070829100839.html FCBarcelona.cat: The Assembly approves Nike deal until 2018]</ref>

* 22 September: The [[Camp Nou]] turns 50-years old with a celebration full of music, light, and colour.<ref>[http://www.fcbarcelona.cat/web/english/noticies/club/temporada07-08/09/n070922101096.html FCBarcelona.cat: Happy birthday Camp Nou!]</ref>

* 22 September: A large reform for the [[Camp Nou]] was revealed. It'll make the Camp Nou bigger, with a movable roof and better facilities.<ref>[http://www.fcbarcelona.cat/web/english/noticies/club/temporada07-08/09/n070922101093.html FCBarcelona.cat: The new Camp Nou]</ref><ref>[http://www.fcbarcelona.cat/web/english/noticies/club/temporada07-08/09/n070922101094.html FCBarcelona.cat: Norman Foster: âItâs a personal challengeâ]</ref><ref>[http://www.fcbarcelona.cat/web/english/noticies/club/temporada07-08/09/n070924101120.html FCBarcelona.cat: Foster: "We want to create the best stadium in the world"]</ref>

* 20 October: [[Bojan KrkiÄ|Bojan]] becomes the youngest ever player to score for the club in [[La Liga]].<ref>[http://www.fcbarcelona.com/web/english/futbol/temporada_07-08/arxiu_partits/lliga/jornada08/Villarreal_Barcelona/partit.html FCBarcelona.cat: Villarreal continue the hoodoo (3-1)]</ref>

* 26 October: BarÃ§a opens a community centre for children in [[Senegal]].<ref>[http://www.fcbarcelona.cat/web/english/noticies/club/temporada07-08/10/n071026101915.html FCBarcelona.cat: Richard Toll support centre opens]</ref>

* 20 March: Copa del Rey ends for Barcelona.<ref>[http://www.fcbarcelona.cat/web/english/noticies/futbol/temporada07-08/03/n080321101880.html FCBarcelona.cat: One defeat ends run]</ref>

* 8 May: [[Frank Rijkaard]] until 30 June; [[Josep Guardiola]] to take over.<ref>[http://www.fcbarcelona.cat/web/english/noticies/futbol/temporada07-08/05/n080508104104.html FCBarcelona.cat: Rijkaard until 30th June; Guardiola to take over.]</ref>

==Players==
===Squad information===
[[Image:Carles Puyol 18abr2007.jpg|right|thumb|100px|[[Carles Puyol]], the current [[Captain (association football)|captain]] and the player with most appearances in the current squad.]]

The squad has reasonably changed in the summer transfer window. The biggest addition was [[Thierry Henry]], with a [[transfer fee]] of [[Euro|â¬]]24 millions. That equals the [[transfer fee]] paid for [[Samuel Eto'o]] in 2004, but just below the â¬30 million paid for [[Ronaldinho]] in 2003. Other additions were [[Ãric Abidal]], [[Yaya TourÃ©]], and [[Gabriel Milito]] that are part of the current [[#Most frequent start|start team]]. On the other end, some important players that were often used last season have left the club, such as, [[Giovanni van Bronckhorst]] and [[Ludovic Giuly]]. Barcelona still used a great number of players developed in its [[youth system]], 9 of 23, and have two new additions this season: [[Giovani Dos Santos|Giovani dos Santos]] and [[Bojan KrkiÄ|Bojan]] (17 years old, the youngest player on the squad).

Most of the players have contracts beyond this end of season, but [[Deco]], an important player, has his contract ending in 2008. The captain is still [[Carles Puyol]], who is from [[FC Barcelona B|Barcelona's youth system]], plays in the first squad since 1999 and currently is the player with the most appearances (268). Currently, the highest scorer is Ronaldinho, with 80 goals. Also Ronaldinho, from August of this year, has a [[European passport]]. On mid-October, [[Samuel Eto'o]] received [[Spain|Spanish]] nationality, making him an [[European Union|EU]] player.<ref>[http://www.fcbarcelona.cat/web/english/noticies/futbol/temporada07-08/10/n071017101231.html FCBarcelona.cat: Eto'o receives Spanish nationality]</ref> The only non-EU player is Yaya TourÃ©. Because Spain ratified the [[Cotonou Agreement]] in 2007, however, TourÃ© is now considered an EU player, as his native country of [[CÃ´te d'Ivoire]] is a [[ACP countries|signatory to that agreement]], and the 2003 [[Kolpak ruling]] extended the [[Bosman ruling]] to nations with an associate trading relationship with the EU.<br />
